                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.209,
                                "byte_start": 100724,
                                "byte_stop": 141580,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion in 76-577, Zacchini against Scripps-Howard Broadcasting will be announced by Mr. Justice White."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.209,
                        "stop": 188.919,
                        "byte_start": 141580,
                        "byte_stop": 856499,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15071,
                            "name": "Byron R. White",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/byron_r_white",
                            "last_name": "White",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2715,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -243367200,
                                    "date_end": 741243600,
                                    "appointing_president": "John F. Kennedy",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2715"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32699,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 55559,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/byron_r_white.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 11396,
                            "identifier": "byron_r_white"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.209,
                                "stop": 14.657,
                                "byte_start": 141580,
                                "byte_stop": 159447,
                                "text": "This case is here from a judgment of the Supreme Court of Ohio."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.657,
                                "stop": 23.475,
                                "byte_start": 159447,
                                "byte_stop": 194660,
                                "text": "It arose when Hugo Zacchini, an entertainer, sued the Scripps-Howard Broadcasting Company."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.475,
                                "stop": 37.333,
                                "byte_start": 194660,
                                "byte_stop": 250144,
                                "text": "The operator of a television station claiming that he has rights under the Ohio law privacy had been violated when the station had broadcast a film of his performance without his consent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 37.333,
                                "stop": 41.175,
                                "byte_start": 250144,
                                "byte_stop": 265504,
                                "text": "Zacchini, interestingly enough has called the \u0022human cannonball\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.175,
                                "stop": 48.364,
                                "byte_start": 265504,
                                "byte_stop": 294239,
                                "text": "His entire act consist of being shot from a cannon into a net some 200 feet away."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.364,
                                "stop": 64.697,
                                "byte_start": 294239,
                                "byte_stop": 359545,
                                "text": "This dispute came about when Zacchini who had been hired to perform on a regular basis at a county fair in Ohio objected to his act being filmed by a television reporter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.697,
                                "stop": 70.959,
                                "byte_start": 359545,
                                "byte_stop": 384623,
                                "text": "The film was made anyway and it was shown on the stations evening broadcast."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.959,
                                "stop": 72.872,
                                "byte_start": 384623,
                                "byte_stop": 392251,
                                "text": "Zacchini sued."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.872,
                                "stop": 79.704,
                                "byte_start": 392251,
                                "byte_stop": 419627,
                                "text": "Under the Ohio privacy law, an entertainer has what is called the \u0022right of publicity.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.704,
                                "stop": 92.946,
                                "byte_start": 419627,
                                "byte_stop": 472603,
                                "text": "That is the exclusive right to publicized and commercially exploit his performances as well as his name and his likeness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.946,
                                "stop": 115.775,
                                "byte_start": 472603,
                                "byte_stop": 563927,
                                "text": "The Supreme Court agreed with Zacchini that he had such right and that has been violated, but held that he had no remedy because as it understood the First and Fourteenth Amendments as construed by the cases in this Court, the television station was constitutionally privileged to do what it did in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.775,
                                "stop": 119.418,
                                "byte_start": 563927,
                                "byte_stop": 578451,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari and we reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.418,
                                "stop": 135.728,
                                "byte_start": 578451,
                                "byte_stop": 643653,
                                "text": "None of our cases has reached this situation and we declined to hold that that a television station is constitutionally privileged to broadcast a performer\u0027s entire act without his consent, whether it\u0027s part of a news broadcast or otherwise."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.728,
                                "stop": 146.275,
                                "byte_start": 643653,
                                "byte_stop": 685867,
                                "text": "Entertainment is important news and thus Scripps-Howard could undoubtedly have broadcast the essential facts of Zacchini\u0027s performance as part of its news broadcast."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.275,
                                "stop": 155.021,
                                "byte_start": 685867,
                                "byte_stop": 720871,
                                "text": "But the First Amendment does not protect the appropriation of an entire act anymore than it would be used for copyright at work."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.021,
                                "stop": 172.836,
                                "byte_start": 720871,
                                "byte_stop": 792133,
                                "text": "Ohio need not have extended a right of publicity to Zacchini and even if it did, it could as a matter of its own law constitution or statutory, privileged the press to do what it did here, privileged to television station to broadcast this film."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.836,
                                "stop": 179.95,
                                "byte_start": 792133,
                                "byte_stop": 820554,
                                "text": "All we hold is the Fourteenth Amendment in which applies the First to the States does not required the State to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.95,
                                "stop": 181.532,
                                "byte_start": 820554,
                                "byte_stop": 826928,
                                "text": "The judgment is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.532,
                                "stop": 188.919,
                                "byte_start": 826928,
                                "byte_stop": 856499,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Powell joined by Justices Brennan and Marshall has filed a dissenting opinion and Mr. Justice Stevens also dissents."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
